<subSubSection id="C37416F0F451FFACFF6569C25B84FD4B" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD1457BF451FFACFF6569C25A22FDDB" blockId="14.[136,1452,158,724]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFF6569C25A1FFE9F" bold="true" box="[189,328,230,256]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Comments:</emphasis>
—In Africa, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFE0A69C2592AFE9E" box="[466,637,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Crotalaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFE0A69C2591EFE9F" box="[466,585,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Crotalaria</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
have been reported as hosts of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFC0869C35EF0FE9E" authority="(Arthur) J. W. Baxter" authorityName="J. W. Baxter" baseAuthorityName="Arthur" box="[976,1447,230,257]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Uromyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="crotalariae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFC0869C35F95FE9F" box="[976,1218,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Uromyces crotalariae</emphasis>
(Arthur) J.W.Baxter
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFF50682F5A4FFEBB" box="[136,280,266,292]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Uromyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="decoratus">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFF50682F5A4FFEBB" box="[136,280,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">U. decoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFE8D682F5907FEBB" authority="Dietel." authorityName="Dietel." box="[341,592,266,292]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Uromyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFE8D682F5AAAFEBB" box="[341,509,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">U. occidentalis</emphasis>
Dietel.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFD8E682F59A2FEBB" box="[598,757,266,292]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Uromyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="crotalariae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFD8E682F59A2FEBB" box="[598,757,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">U. crotalariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by teliospores that can be 20–27 µm long and 27–32 µm broad or 24–30 × 20–27 μm (versus 26–32 × 18–20 µm in the specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF451FFACFBA5680A5F95FED6" box="[1149,1218,302,329]" name="Benin" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Benin</collectingCountry>
) and have verrucose to echinulate ornamentation (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF451FFACFE0A687659F9FEF2" author="Hennen, J. F. &amp; Figueiredo, M. B. &amp; de Carvalho, Jr. A. A. &amp; Hennen, P. G." box="[466,686,338,365]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" refId="ref11810" refString="Hennen, J. F., Figueiredo, M. B., de Carvalho, Jr. A. A. &amp; Hennen, P. G. (2005) Catalogue of the species of plant rust fungi (Uredinales) of Brazil. Instituto de Pesquisas, Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro: Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, 490 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Hennen 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFDEB68775932FEF3" box="[563,613,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">et al</emphasis>
. 2005
</bibRefCitation>
) in contrast to flat warts partly in striae in the present specimen. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFA4868775A58FE0F" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Uromyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFA4868775A58FE0F" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">U. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFE27685359C7FE0E" box="[511,656,375,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Lupinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFE276853590EFE0F" box="[511,601,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Lupinus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF451FFACFCD968525860FE0F" box="[769,823,374,400]" name="United States of America" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF451FFACFC9068525898FE0F" author="Dietel, P." box="[840,975,374,400]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" pagination="95 - 99" refId="ref11235" refString="Dietel, P. (1903) Uber die Uromyces - Arten auf Lupinen. Hedwigia Beiblatter 42: 95 - 99." type="journal article" year="1903">Dietel 1903</bibRefCitation>
) and was mentioned once on a species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFF5068BE5BA8FE2B" baseAuthorityName="Farr &amp; Rossman" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[136,255,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Crotalaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFF5068BE5BA8FE2B" box="[136,255,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Crotalaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF451FFACFEF868BE5A23FE2B" box="[288,372,410,436]" name="Nigeria" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF451FFACFE5A68BE5956FE2B" author="Eboh, D. O." box="[386,513,410,436]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" pagination="1077 - 1085" refId="ref11441" refString="Eboh, D. O. (1978) A taxonomic survey of Nigerian rust fungi: Uredinales Nigerianensis-I. Mycologia 70: 1077 - 1085. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3759139" type="journal article" year="1978">Eboh 1978</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF451FFACFD7168BE5817FE2B" author="Dietel, P." box="[681,832,410,436]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" pagination="95 - 99" refId="ref11235" refString="Dietel, P. (1903) Uber die Uromyces - Arten auf Lupinen. Hedwigia Beiblatter 42: 95 - 99." type="journal article" year="1903">Dietel (1903)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFC9368BF58A4FE2B" box="[843,1011,410,436]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Uromyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFC9368BF58A4FE2B" box="[843,1011,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">U. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by densely (not striate) warty teliospores measuring 17–26 × 16–21 µm (versus 26–32 × 18–20 µm in the 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF451FFACFBFD689A5F3FFE47" box="[1061,1128,446,472]" name="Benin" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Benin</collectingCountry>
specimen). We consider that the identification proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF451FFACFE3868C6593AFE63" author="Eboh, D. O." box="[480,621,482,508]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" pagination="1077 - 1085" refId="ref11441" refString="Eboh, D. O. (1978) A taxonomic survey of Nigerian rust fungi: Uredinales Nigerianensis-I. Mycologia 70: 1077 - 1085. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3759139" type="journal article" year="1978">Eboh (1978)</bibRefCitation>
is erroneous and that the specimen collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF451FFACFB5168C65F8AFE63" box="[1161,1245,482,508]" name="Nigeria" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
corresponds to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFA4868C75BA1FDBF" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Uromyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="decoratus">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFA4868C75BA1FDBF" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">U. decoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because he described urediniospores similar to those presented here for 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF451FFACFBEE6B225F2EFDBF" box="[1078,1145,518,544]" name="Benin" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Benin</collectingCountry>
as well as teliospores with warts partly in striae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD1457BF451FFACFF656B6A5B84FD4B" blockId="14.[136,1452,158,724]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">
The present specimen is identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F451FFACFDB06B6B59AEFDF7" box="[616,761,590,616]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Uromyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="decoratus">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFDB06B6B59AEFDF7" box="[616,761,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">U. decoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the presence of teliospores with flat warts partly in lines and sizes similar to those reported for the 
<typeStatus id="54D5FBD9F451FFACFD436B57599CFD12" box="[667,715,627,653]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">type</typeStatus>
(20–28 × 14–20 µm; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF451FFACFC196B565FD8FD13" author="Sydow, H. &amp; Sydow, P. &amp; Butler, E. J." box="[961,1167,626,653]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" pagination="485 - 515" refId="ref13851" refString="Sydow, H., Sydow, P. &amp; Butler, E. J. (1907) Fungi Indiae Orientalis. Part II. Annual Mycology 5: 485 - 515." type="journal article" year="1907">
Sydow 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F451FFACFBCE6B575F1FFD13" box="[1046,1096,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">et al</emphasis>
. 1907
</bibRefCitation>
) or approximately 19–31 × 14–20 µm as measured from diverse specimens by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF451FFACFD026BB258D7FD2E" author="Bouhot, D." box="[730,896,662,689]" pageId="14" pageNumber="141" pagination="274 - 300" refId="ref10645" refString="Bouhot, D. (1966) Quelques champignons phytopathogenes nouveaux ou peu connus au Senegal. Bulletin de la Societe Mycologique de France 82: 274 - 300." type="journal article" year="1966">Bouhot (1966)</bibRefCitation>
. This species is reported here for the first time for 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF451FFACFF506B9E5B99FD4B" box="[136,206,698,724]" name="Benin" pageId="14" pageNumber="141">Benin</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
